The paper proposes a novel formulation of variational autoencoders to improve the generation of multimodal data. This involves learning data-dependent conditional priors to differentiate between individual mixture components and allow for generations from distributional data clusters. This work involves machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves computer vision (CV) techniques, as it deals with generating images from multimodal data. Therefore, cs.CV is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves neural networks (NE) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques, as it deals with unsupervised learning of latent categories encoding the multimodality of the original data. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.CL are also possible sub-categories.
